http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The standards are the targets all students need to meet at the proficient level by the end of each grade level. The standards will be presented in two formats. The first format organizes the standards by grade level so a student, parent, classroom teacher, administrator, or local school board member can quickly review what learning is expected at each specific grade. The Bloom's Taxonomy level of cognitive challenge is listed in the standard document to make clear the level at which each standard should be assessed.
